(versions.) 126 282 T
-0.14 (The FFIM includes a large, comprehensive set of shapes defined by \322feature_sweeps\323.) 126 262 P
4.11 (There are three types of feature_sweeps: axisymmetric, along, and in_out. An) 126 248 P
0.58 (axisymmetric_feature_sweep is basically a solid of rotation. The other two types are,) 126 234 P
0.67 (roughly speaking, the solid you get if you sweep some type of planar profile along a) 126 220 P
0.95 (path, keeping the plane normal to the path. The along_feature_sweep is meant to be) 126 206 P
3.53 (along the surface of an existing solid, and is made with an open profile. The) 126 192 P
0.48 (in_out_feature_sweep is intended to dig into or stick out of the surface of an existing) 126 178 P
(solid. The feature sweeps come with a variety of methods of edge and end blending.) 126 164 T
