-0.1 (MRSEV technical issues are listed but not discussed here. A discussion of these issues) 126 506 P
0.45 (is the subject of a separate paper [Kramer92a]. The reader may find it helpful to read) 126 492 P
1.08 (that paper in conjunction with reading this one. The resolution of each issue for the) 126 478 P
(purposes of the library described in this paper is given after each issue.) 126 464 T
(1.) 126 444 T
3.12 (How does a MRSEV relate to a machining operation? - Each metal cutting) 144 444 P
3.14 (machining operation in a process plan will refer to a MRSEV. The volume) 144 430 P
-0.48 (described by a MRSEV should have no material in it when the machining operation) 144 416 P
(is complete, and the operation should remove no material outside the volume.) 144 402 T
(2.) 126 382 T
0.31 (How should patterns, groups and replications be handled? - See the description of) 144 382 P
(the library.) 144 368 T
(3.) 126 348 T
-0.51 (How do MRSEVs relate to workpiece shape? - MRSEVs are defined independently) 144 348 P
(of workpiece shape.) 144 334 T
(4.) 126 314 T
(Should MRSEVs carry machining information?- No.) 144 314 T
(5.) 126 294 T
0.53 (Should the MRSEVs be from a fixed library of canonical types or should they be) 144 294 P
(defined as needed? - Use a fixed library.) 144 280 T
(6.) 126 260 T
(Is air allowed in a MRSEV? - Yes.) 144 260 T
(7.) 126 240 T
-0.15 (How can MRSEVs be linked to design data? - This issue has not been addressed in) 144 240 P
(building the library.) 144 226 T
(8.) 126 206 T
0.69 (Should MRSEVs be defined as closed volumes or as open ones, or allow both? -) 144 206 P
(The library uses closed volumes.) 144 192 T
(9.) 126 172 T
4 (Should MRSEVs be defined entirely unambiguously, or is some ambiguity) 144 172 P
-0.06 (desirable?- In general, ambiguity is undesirable. The library leaves ambiguity only) 144 158 P
(in the case of thread timing and, optionally, the end radius of edge_cuts.) 144 144 T
(10.) 126 124 T
-0.27 (What machining operations should the MRSEVs support? - The library supports 3-) 144 124 P
(axis machining.) 144 110 T
