0.69 (Many of the shapes in the library are defined with the aid of a \322profile\323. Profiles are) 126 622 P
1.53 (used in the library both as two dimensional shapes which may be swept or rotated) 126 608 P
-0.4 (through space to make a solid, and as paths through space along which other profiles or) 126 594 P
(cross sections can be swept.) 126 580 T
0.94 (The STEP Form Features Information Model \050FFIM\051 and the Geometry Model both) 126 560 P
0.43 (provide resources for defining profiles. This section assumes that some method using) 126 546 P
7.24 (those resources can be implemented, but does not describe any specific) 126 532 P
(implementation. An implementation using the FFIM is given in Appendix B.) 126 518 T
