(General_Profile) 126 495 T
0 F
-0.32 (A \322general_profile\323 is defined to be an ordered collection of arcs of circles and straight) 126 475 P
-0.35 (line segments lying in a plane. The elements \050arcs of circles and straight line segments\051) 126 461 P
0.39 (of a profile are numbered with consecutive integers, starting with 1. There must be at) 126 447 P
1.62 (least one element. The elements are joined end-to-end to form a continuous curve.) 126 433 P
3.11 (Adjacent straight line segments may not be colinear unless they go in opposite) 126 419 P
1.32 (directions. Adjacent arcs of circles may not have the same center unless they go in) 126 405 P
(opposite directions.) 126 391 T
-0.68 (If there are three or more elements, or if there are two elements but only one pair of ends) 126 371 P
0.52 (is connected, this establishes a positive direction for the profile - going from element) 126 357 P
0.63 (one towards element 2. If there is only one element, or if there are two elements and) 126 343 P
-0.16 (both pairs of ends are connected, a positive direction is assigned some other way \050such) 126 329 P
-0.4 (as by using the definition of the underlying curve of the first element\051. The \322first point\323) 126 315 P
-0.23 (of the profile is the point at the negative direction end of the first element, and the \322last) 126 301 P
-0.02 (point\323 of the profile is the point at the positive direction end of the last element. These) 126 287 P
(conventions lend themselves to straightforward implementations.) 126 273 T
1 F
