(Other Types of Profile) 126 250 T
0 F
-0.02 (Other types of profile are subtypes of general_profile. If the last point of a profile is in) 126 230 P
-0.35 (the same place as the first point, the profile is called a \322closed_profile\323. Otherwise, it is) 126 216 P
1.88 (called an \322open_profile\323. If a closed_profile does not intersect itself, it is called a) 126 202 P
-0.42 (\322nice_closed_profile\323. If an open_profile does not intersect itself and has the following) 126 188 P
-0.53 (character, it is called a nice_open_profile \050see Figure 17\051: Let a straight line L be drawn) 126 174 P
-0.74 (between the first point P and the last point Q of the profile. The profile does not intersect) 126 160 P
-0.2 (L except at P and Q. If a line M is drawn perpendicular to L at any point, then: \0501\051 if M) 126 146 P
-0.02 (intersects L outside the segment between P and Q, it does not intersect the profile, and) 126 132 P
0.17 (\0502\051 if M intersects L inside the segment or at P or Q, it intersects the profile at exactly) 126 118 P
(one point or it overlaps exactly one straight line segment that is part of the profile.) 126 104 T
