0.94 (A hole is a right circular cylinder with an optional end condition at the bottom. The) 126 539 P
-0.11 (native coordinate system of a hole has its origin at the center of the bottom, with the z-) 126 525 P
(axis on the axis of the cylinder, pointing toward the top.) 126 511 T
0.7 (End conditions on holes include conical end, round end, flat blend, and round blend.) 126 491 P
0.4 (The end condition of a hole may use up the entire length of the cylinder, but may not) 126 477 P
-0.13 (require more than that. Thus, a hole may be purely hemispherical or conical. If the end) 126 463 P
(condition is a blend, it may not blend away the entire bottom of the hole.) 126 449 T
